## Polymorphic Associations

One model belongs to multiple other models.

```ruby
# app/models/comment.rb
class Comment < ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :commentable, polymorphic: true
  belongs_to :user
end

# app/models/article.rb
class Article < ApplicationRecord
  has_many :comments, as: :commentable, dependent: :destroy
end

# app/models/video.rb
class Video < ApplicationRecord
  has_many :comments, as: :commentable, dependent: :destroy
end
```

**Database Structure:**
```ruby
# comments table
- id
- commentable_id    # ID of article or video
- commentable_type  # 'Article' or 'Video'
- user_id
- body
- created_at
- updated_at
```

**Usage:**
```ruby
article = Article.first
article.comments.create(user: user, body: "Great article!")

video = Video.first
video.comments.create(user: user, body: "Nice video!")

comment = Comment.first
comment.commentable  # Returns Article or Video
comment.commentable_type  # 'Article' or 'Video'
```

